{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"weak","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"id<MLNMapSnapshotterDelegate>","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:Qoobjc(pl)MLNMapSnapshotterDelegate"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"delegate","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The delegate is responsible for responding to significant changes during the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snapshotting process, such as the style loading. Implement a delegate to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"customize the style that is depicted by the snapshot."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You set the delegate after initializing the snapshotter but before receiving"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the snapshot, typically before starting the snapshot. The snapshotter keeps a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"weak reference to its delegate, so you must keep a strong reference to it to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that your style customizations apply."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The snapshotter’s delegate."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNMapSnapshotter(py)delegate","symbolKind":"property","fragments":[{"text":"delegate","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"delegate","roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"delegate","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter\/delegate","in